text: Acoma sexfoliata is a species of beetles first discovered by Saylor in 1948.Saylor L.W. (1948) Contributions toward a knowledge of the insect fauna of Lower California. No. 10. Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae, Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences (4)24:337-374 No sub-species are listed at Catalogue of Life.Scarabs: World Scarabaeidae Database.
